Detailed Description

Class holding a NavServerProt, v10+, param.

All complex values (16 bit, 32 bit) are considered to have the most significant byte first. All data is in network order that is.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum NParam::NParam_t
 

The types of NParam content, not used directly.

Enumeration values:
Bool  The length may be 0 or 1.

If 0 length then value is true. If length is 1 then the value is false if the byte is 0 true if not.

Byte  Length of 1, values 0-255 are possible.
Uint16  Length of 2, values 0-65535 are possible.
Uint32  Length of 4, values 0-4294967295 are possible.
Int32  Length of 4, values -2147483648 to 2147483647 are possible.
String  Array of bytes ended by an null-byte, integer value of 0.

Strings are utf-8 encoded.

Byte_array  An array of length bytes.
Uint16_array  An array of length/2 uint16s.
Uint32_array  An array of length/4 uint32s.
Int32_array  An array of length/4 int32s.
